**A:** Due to the way that the saving system has been implemented, we can currently only make optimizations to savedata usage.

**A:** This is a work-in-progress at the moment. Stay tuned.

creations-chat 2023-07-13 08:25:23 I would build the sections individually then install the onto the aircraft as it’s easier to improve them if it’s all spaced apart, i.e the nose looks abit wonky, use a motor lock tower or something to separate it in build mode then use a different combination of blocks using motor lock and half blocks  as the curtain version looks very rushed.

here’s my old build as an example 

https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/384025409945337856/843274119247560733/image0.png
creations-chat 2023-07-13 08:30:07 maybe try motorlocking onto existing parts but keep in mind it does look extremely messy and upgrading it will be difficult, I suggest having another motorlock tower going into another direction to accommodate for the upgrades
creations-chat 2023-07-13 08:36:44 For painting it, you could use the default plastic material then paining it so the leading edge appears to have highlights like increasing the value by afew values and make sure to blend it into the rest of the wing so it feels natural and not artificially painted brighter using slight deviations in the paint job, remember less is more
creations-chat 2023-07-13 08:40:31 try experimenting with the nose in a different save or in the corner of the plot. I would try to motor lock different parts together such as half blocks, disconnector (heads and bases) and really anything else as the end result tends to be rather different to what you started with. see what happens and try to mix and match them to create a nose or any other component

also, being able to know what a motorlocked build will look like without having to load it is an incredible skill to have as it saves time but it’s not a mandatory requirement to have to be a “good builder” like any other skill
creations-chat 2023-07-13 08:47:33 It may have been caused by the cockpit glass shape as it warps everything around it but I wouldn’t worry too much, I would take note from this current project and use it to improve all the projects you’ll make in the future, I wish you all the best in your efforts and I hope you have a great day
